			<h3 class="fw-title"><a name="48173020"></a><!-- ParagraphTitleStart -->Welcome to the online home of horror-suspense author JOSEPH ARMSTEAD, creator of the vampiric MOON-CHOSEN vampires and the dreaded INFERNALS.   <!-- ParagraphTitleEnd --></h3>
			<div class="fw-text"><!-- ParagraphBodyStart --><p>"...`But I don't want to go among mad people,' Alice remarked.<br>`Oh, you can't help that,' said the Cat: `we're all mad here. I'm mad.&nbsp; You're mad.'<br>`How do you know I'm mad?' said Alice.<br>`You must be,' said the Cat, `or you wouldn't have come here.'"</p>
<p>--- Lewis Carroll, from Alice in Wonderland</p>
<p>***</p>
<p><img src="https://webzoom.freewebs.com/jarmsteadsnocturnes/dreamstime_m_12561678.jpg" border="0"></p>
<p><br>They told you not to go there.&nbsp; It was not a healthy place.&nbsp; Bad things happened there, things that could change you in ways you never expected.&nbsp; Hard, hurtful things that scarred people for life.&nbsp; They said to stay away.&nbsp; You couldn't.&nbsp; It haunted your every thought.&nbsp;&nbsp; You daydreamed about it.&nbsp; While you slept its strange music haunted your nightmares.&nbsp;&nbsp; Macabre images danced unbidden across your mind's eye and you couldn't shake the dark feeling that you'd visited someplace just this side of Hell.</p>
<p>It excited you.</p>
<p>You looked.&nbsp; You saw it.&nbsp; There, in the moonlight, larger than life and twice as angry.&nbsp; You didn't want to, but you did.&nbsp; You saw.&nbsp; And from that moment you knew your world had changed...</p>
<p>Because when you saw it, it saw YOU --- and it smiled.</p>
<p>Fangs of purest alabaster shone in the moon's cold glare and you knew you had to feel their piercing touch on your skin... You wanted it.</p>
<p>They told you not to go there.&nbsp; It was not a healthy place.</p>
<p>***</p>
<p><img src="http://counters.freewebs.com/Members/Counters/counter.jsp?userid=11357216&amp;name=jarmsteadsnocturnes"></p><!-- ParagraphBodyEnd --></div>
